ePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528274\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528274\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 27, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hly1665702657301.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hly1665702657301.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hly1665702657301.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hly1665702657301\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n /key \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"hly1665702657301___key_486570\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Build keyboard translation tables in a character-based interface.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"hly1665702657301__topic_d149891e1_d149892e1_d149893e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149894e1_d149895e1_d149896e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/key</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hly1665702657301__topic_d107942e1_d107943e1_d107944e1_d107945e1_d107946e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d276572e65\">\n                  \n Description\n </h2>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"hly1665702657301__note_w2450ab1b5b5b3_w2451ab1b5b5_w2452ab1b5_w2453ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/key</span> functionality is intended only for character-based\n            interfaces. It cannot be used with Windows because Windows handles keyboard codes in a\n            radically different manner. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pro1665702657373.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pro1665702657373.html\">X11 Keyboards</a>.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149900e1_d149901e1_d149902e1\">The escape sequences sent by a keyboard are often rather cryptic and difficult to decipher. Instead of entering each sequence, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/key</span> switch creates keyboard translation table definitions by asking a series of questions, which builds a keyboard translation table from keyboard input to <var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149903e1_d149904e1_d149905e1\">This facility is designed to provide a good start for defining keyboard translation tables; it is not intended for defining whole tables. For example, each macro can only be defined once and special font characters are not included.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149906e1_d149907e1_d149908e1\">To create mappings, you press the key or series of keys for each function,</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149909e1_d149910e1_d149911e1\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/key</span> switch to create a keyboard translation table, then use the following command line switches to compile it:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149912e1_d149913e1_d149914e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/tra</span>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/fil</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hly1665702657301__topic_d107947e1_d107948e1_d107949e1_d107950e1_d107951e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d276572e115\">\n                  \n Using /key\n </h2>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hly1665702657301__li_d52130e1_d52131e1_d52132e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149918e1_d149919e1_d149920e1\">Run the Uniface IDE using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/key</span>\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">ide /key mykeys</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149921e1_d149922e1_d149923e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/key</span>facility starts by giving its general syntax rules.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hly1665702657301__li_d52133e1_d52134e1_d52135e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149924e1_d149925e1_d149926e1\">Define up to ten macros which can be used in further definitions.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hly1665702657301__li_d52136e1_d52137e1_d52138e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149927e1_d149928e1_d149929e1\">In response to the prompts, enter a keystroke or series of keystrokes for each Uniface function. Each function can have any number of keystroke combinations.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149930e1_d149931e1_d149932e1\">A keyboard translation table definition is created and saves in the specified file.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hly1665702657301__li_d52139e1_d52140e1_d52141e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149933e1_d149934e1_d149935e1\">After creating the file, do one of the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hly1665702657301__li_d52142e1_d52143e1_d52144e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149936e1_d149937e1_d149938e1\">If you have Uniface running on a system for which you already have a keyboard translation, create a new table and use the ^INS_FILE structure editor function to read in the file. (The SUPER key combination for ^INS_FILE is GOLD Space I X.)</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hly1665702657301__li_d52145e1_d52146e1_d52147e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149939e1_d149940e1_d149941e1\">If you do not have another keyboard\n                        translation available, compile the table using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/tra</span>\n                        command line switch. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">ide /tra /fil mykeys</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149942e1_d149943e1_d149944e1\">This command creates a table called\n                        TERMFILE. Declare TERMFILE as your keyboard in the assignment file which you\n                        use to start the Uniface IDE. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$KEYBOARD = TERMFILE</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hly1665702657301__p_d149945e1_d149946e1_d149947e1\">You can give the new keyboard\n                        translation table TERMFILE another name.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ltj1703097709703.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Keyboard Translation Table Syntax</a><p>Keyboard translation tables map input codes from keyboards or database to logical Uniface functions and characters.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dom1695191702402.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Macro Definitions</a><p>The translation table compiler supports up to ten macros, ^M0 through ^M9, for commonly-used combinations.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528274\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528274\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/key Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 27, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 /key Build keyboard translation tables in a character-based interface. /key FileName Description Note: The /key functionality is intended only for character-based interfaces. It cannot be used with Windows because Windows handles keyboard codes in a radically different manner. For more information, see X11 Keyboards . The escape sequences sent by a keyboard are often rather cryptic and difficult to decipher. Instead of entering each sequence, the /key switch creates keyboard translation table definitions by asking a series of questions, which builds a keyboard translation table from keyboard input to FileName . This facility is designed to provide a good start for defining keyboard translation tables; it is not intended for defining whole tables. For example, each macro can only be defined once and special font characters are not included. To create mappings, you press the key or series of keys for each function, Use the /key switch to create a keyboard translation table, then use the following command line switches to compile it: /tra /fil FileName Using /key Run the Uniface IDE using /key ide /key mykeys Copy The /key facility starts by giving its general syntax rules. Define up to ten macros which can be used in further definitions. In response to the prompts, enter a keystroke or series of keystrokes for each Uniface function. Each function can have any number of keystroke combinations. A keyboard translation table definition is created and saves in the specified file. After creating the file, do one of the following: If you have Uniface running on a system for which you already have a keyboard translation, create a new table and use the ^INS_FILE structure editor function to read in the file. (The SUPER key combination for ^INS_FILE is GOLD Space I X.) If you do not have another keyboard translation available, compile the table using the /tra command line switch. For example: ide /tra /fil mykeys Copy This command creates a table called TERMFILE. Declare TERMFILE as your keyboard in the assignment file which you use to start the Uniface IDE. For example: $KEYBOARD = TERMFILE Copy You can give the new keyboard translation table TERMFILE another name. Related Links Keyboard Translation Table Syntax Keyboard translation tables map input codes from keyboards or database to logical Uniface functions and characters. Macro Definitions The translation table compiler supports up to ten macros, ^M0 through ^M9, for commonly-used combinations. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}